videos.description: Michigan State's Miles Bridges finds the ball and runs it up the court for the dunk.
videos.headline: Bridges gets the loose ball and slams it in

videos.description: Derrick Walton Jr. draws defenders and finds the rolling Mark Donnal for the layup plus the foul.
videos.headline: Michigan's Walton with the nice bounce pass leading to and-1 layup

videos.description: Michigan's Moritz Wagner gets the steal and dunk on the other end.
videos.headline: Defense leads to offense for big Michigan dunk

videos.description: D. J Wilson dunks it on the defender and gets a technical foul after he stares him down.
videos.headline: Michigan's Wilson with the stare-down after big dunk

videos.description: Michigan's Moe Wagner gets the big time dunk and gets the foul as well.
videos.headline: Michigan's Wagner throws one down

videos.description: Michigan's Duncan Robinson gets the ball at the corner and makes the 3-pointer as time expires in the first half.
videos.headline: Michigan's Robinson drains 3-pointer as first half time expires

videos.description: Michigan's coach John Beilein talks about teams defensive performance and about the technical fouls that occurred in the game.
videos.headline: Michigan's coach John Beilein talks about his teams strong first half defensive performance

videos.description: Miles Bridges goes up high and finishes strong with the alley-oop jam.
videos.headline: Bridges gets up high for the alley-oop

videos.description: Derrick Walton Jr. talks about what this win means to him and how important it was to get the victory over Michigan State tonight.
videos.headline: Michigan's Walton talks about the significant win over Michigan State tonight
